# Write a program that prompts the user to enter the minutes (e.g., 1 billion), and displays the number of years and days for
#the minutes. For simplicity, assume a year has 365 days.

mint = eval(input("Enter the number of minutes: "))
min_y = mint//525600
min_d1 = mint%525600
min_d2 = min_d1//1440
min_h = min_d2//24
min_m = min_h/60

print(f"{mint} minutes is approximately {min_y} years and {min_d2} days")
